<Base title="We Are a Dream — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>We Are a Dream</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">Kunsthalle Ost, Leipzig | 2024</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>The exhibition draws inspiration from Ursula Le Guin's science fiction novel <em>The Lathe of Heaven</em>, set in a dystopian retrofuturistic city where surveillance and chemical control dominate human experience. The protagonist discovers his dreams manifest in reality, prompting him to resist sleep as "one of the last outposts of rebellion and individual freedom."</p>
      <p>Liput creates an immersive space exploring sleep as resistance—a realm for "unlearning, forgetting, losing control" from harsh political and social conditions. The exhibition features monochrome drawings on paper, expressive fabric installation, ceramic and crocheted embroidered forms.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Artist:</strong> Aleksandra Liput</p>
      <p><strong>Curator:</strong> Michalina Sablik</p>
      <p><strong>Partners:</strong> Polish Institute Berlin, Adam Mickiewicz Institute</p>
      <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> Kuba Mozolewski</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
